description: Timothée Chalamet’s A Complete Unknown, a biographical musical on Bob Dylan’s early years, debuted in theatres on December 25, 2024, with its India premiere on February 28, 2025. The film, directed by James Mangold, explores Dylan’s rise in the music industry and his controversial shift to electric rock. Following its successful run, A Complete Unknown will be available for streaming on Hulu and JioHotstar from March 27, 2025. With 8 Academy Award nominations and a 7.4 IMDb rating, the film continues to captivate audiences worldwide.
title: A Complete Unknown OTT Release Date: When and Where to Watch Timothée Chalamet’s Biopic

description: New images from the decommissioned Atacama Cosmology Telescope offer the most detailed view of the cosmic microwave background. The data reveals early cosmic structures, tracks primordial gas movement, and refines estimates of the universe’s total mass. While supporting existing models, it does not resolve the Hubble tension. Researchers are now looking to the Simons Observatory for further insights into cosmic evolution.
title: Atacama Telescope Reveals Most Detailed Cosmic Microwave Background Yet

description: Brahma Anandam, the emotional family drama starring veteran comedian Brahmanandam and his son Raja Goutham, is now streaming on Aha. The film, directed by RVS Nikhil, explores the heartfelt bond between a grandfather and his grandson. After its theatrical release on February 14, 2025, the film struggled at the box office but is now set to reach a wider audience through its digital release. With a strong supporting cast and moving performances, Brahma Anandam is a touching watch for family drama lovers
title: Brahma Anandam Now Streaming on Aha: Everything You Need to Know

description: Iguanas undertook a remarkable 5,000-mile journey from North America to Fiji around 34 million years ago. According to a new genetic study, these reptiles floated on rafts of vegetation, possibly due to extreme weather events. The research, published in PNAS, found that Fiji’s iguanas are closely related to North American species, contradicting earlier theories. Their resistance to dehydration and starvation may have helped them survive. The study aligns their arrival with the islands’ formation, shedding light on one of the longest transoceanic migrations by a land species.
title: Iguanas Travelled 5,000 Miles to Fiji on Rafts 34 Million Years Ago

description: Mount Spurr, a stratovolcano west of Anchorage, has shown rising seismic activity, gas emissions, and melting snow, suggesting magma movement beneath the surface. Scientists at the Alaska Volcano Observatory believe an eruption is becoming more likely, with historical eruptions in 1953 and 1992 at Crater Peak having sent ash plumes over Anchorage. Experts are monitoring for volcanic tremor, which could indicate an imminent eruption.
title: Mount Spurr Volcano in Alaska Shows Signs of Possible Eruption

description: NASA and SpaceX successfully completed the return of Crew-9 astronauts aboard Crew Dragon Freedom. The spacecraft undocked from the ISS early on March 18 and began its descent after a scheduled deorbit burn. The crew—Nick Hague, Aleksandr Gorbunov, Sunita Williams, and Barry Wilmore—landed in the Gulf of Mexico after traveling millions of miles in orbit. Hague and Gorbunov spent 171 days in space, while Williams and Wilmore completed a 286-day mission. Future crew landings under NASA’s program may shift to the Pacific Ocean.
title: NASA, SpaceX Crew-9 Returns on Crew Dragon Freedom After 171 Days in Space

description: Rocket Lab has successfully launched the last five satellites for Kinéis' "Internet of Things" constellation. The mission, called "High Five," took off on March 17 from the company's New Zealand site. The Electron rocket deployed the satellites into a 404-mile orbit, completing the 25-satellite network. This system enhances global connectivity by enabling real-time data transmission for industries such as maritime tracking and environmental monitoring. This marks Rocket Lab’s fourth successful launch of 2025, following a steady increase in its operational frequency.
title: Rocket Lab Launches Final Five Satellites for Kinéis' IoT Constellation

description: After a successful theatrical run, Aadhi Pinisetty’s Sabdham is set to stream on Prime Video from March 28, 2025, as per reports. Directed by Arivazhagan Venkatachalam, the film follows a paranormal investigator uncovering eerie deaths in a medical college. Lakshmi Menon plays a sceptical surgeon who clashes with his beliefs. The supernatural thriller has received positive reviews for its gripping narrative and atmospheric tension. The official confirmation from Prime Video is awaited.
title: Sabdham OTT Release Date: When and Where to Watch Aadhi Pinisetty’s Horror Thriller

description: Telugu crime thriller Touch Me Not brings a suspenseful story of psychometry and crime-solving to JioHotstar. Starring Navdeep and Dheekshith Shetty, the show follows a teenager who can unlock past secrets by touching objects, leading him into a dangerous serial killer case. Directed by Ramana Teja, the series is an official adaptation of the Korean drama He is Psychometric. The show will premiere on April 4, 2025, offering a thrilling watch for mystery lovers.
title: Touch Me Not Telugu OTT Release Date: When and Where to Watch it Online?

description: New research using Keck Observatory’s instruments confirms that the orbit of Wolf-Rayet 104 is tilted 30-40 degrees away from Earth, lowering concerns about a possible gamma-ray burst. Previously, it was believed that the system’s alignment could pose a risk. However, spectroscopy data now challenges these assumptions, raising new questions about how the star’s dust plume forms. This unexpected finding provides relief while introducing fresh mysteries about the star’s structure and wind interactions.
title: Wolf-Rayet 104's Orbit Tilt Reduces Gamma-Ray Burst Threat, Study Finds

description: Vera Rubin Observatory Installs World's Largest Digital Camera for Sky Survey
title: World's Largest Digital Camera Installed on Vera Rubin Observatory for Cosmic Exploration

description: Binance users can now participate in selecting which new tokens should be listed for trading on the platform. The exchange, through this feature, expects to address the challenge of identifying legitimate crypto tokens from the flood of altcoins in the market, through community efforts.
title: Binance’s ‘Vote to List’ Feature for Community Polling on Token Listing Goes Live

description: Infinix is gearing up to bring down the curtains on XOS 15 — its take on the latest Android 15 operating system (OS) — with the launch of the Infinix Note 50X globally today (Thursday) and in India on March 27. While XOS 15 is currently still in beta, we explored its key additions and found several exciting features that bring a fresh touch to the Android experience.
title: XOS 15 Beta: 3 Features We Liked and 1 That Could Be Better

description: Motorola Razr 60 is reportedly making its way to the market soon. The launch date is yet to be officially confirmed by Motorola, but ahead of it, renders and key specifications including colour options of the phone have been tipped online. The Motorola Razr 50 successor is said to come in three colourways with a 6.7-inch inner display. The Motorola Razr 60 could run on a MediaTek Dimensity 7400X chipset.
title: Motorola Razr 60 Design, Specifications Leaked; Said to Get MediaTek Dimensity 7400X Chipset, 4,500mAh Battery

description: xAI, the Elon Musk-led artificial intelligence (AI) firm behind Grok, released a new application programming interface (API) on Wednesday. The new API is unique as it is the first developer tool that supports image generation. The company has lately been focused on developers and has released as many as five APIs since the first one arrived in November 2024.
title: xAI Launches New Grok API for Developers With Image Generation Capability

description: The Dubai Land Department (DLD) has launched the pilot phase of its “Real Estate Tokenisation Project”. The pilot will be overseen by Marwan Ahmed Bin Ghalita, Director General of the DLD. Industry players from Dubai’s private and public sectors will be invited to participate in discussions related to asset tokenisation in the coming days.
title: Dubai Launches Pilot Phase of Real Estate Tokenisation Project for Web3, Real Estate Collaboration

description: Gemini is getting two new artificial intelligence (AI) features, Google announced on Tuesday. The Mountain View-based tech giant is adding Canvas, an interactive space that lets human users and AI collaborate on projects involving documents and coding-related tasks. Another feature making its way to Gemini is Audio Overview, which lets users generate an engaging podcast-like audio discussion based on documents, slides, and Deep Research reports.
title: Gemini Is Getting Upgraded With Audio Overview and Canvas Features

description: HMD Barbie Phone has been launched in India. The feature phone comes with a flip design and a 2.8-inch inner display. The phone also gets a 1.77-inch QQVGA outer screen that doubles as a mirror. The handset is offered in a single pink shade and ships in a pink jewellery box-like case with a pink charging case, pink battery, and accessories like additional back covers, stickers, lanyards and charms.
title: HMD Barbie Phone With 2.8-Inch Main Display, Themed Accessories Launched in India: Price, Specifications

description: Huawei Pura X has been launched in China as the latest foldable phone from the Shenzen-based manufacturer with a unique design. The clamshell foldable phone has a 6.3-inch inner screen with a 16:10 aspect ratio that's the widest on a clamshell foldable. It also gets a 3.5-inch external display and a triple camera setup. The handset runs on HarmonyOS 5.0.1 and packs up to 16GB RAM with up to 1TB storage.
title: Huawei Pura X Foldable Phone With 6.3-Inch 16:10 Wide Inner Screen Launched: Price, Specifications

description: CMF Phone 2 is believed to hit shelves soon as a successor to last year's CMF Phone 1. The Nothing sub-brand is yet to confirm its existence, but ahead of it, alleged renders of the phone have leaked online. The renders show the rear panel design of the CMF Phone 2, suggesting a redesigned rear camera unit comprising three sensors.
title: CMF Phone 2 Alleged Hands-on Images Leak Online; Suggests Triple Rear Camera Setup

description: Infinix Note 50X 5G is confirmed to get a MediaTek Dimensity 7300 Ultimate SoC and run on Android 15-based XOS 15 out-of-the-box. The design and colour options of the model have been revealed as well. Ahead of the handset's India launch on March 27, the company has now also confirmed the battery size and charging details. Meanwhile, more details regarding the battery and the probable price range of the Note 50X have leaked.
title: Infinix Note 50X 5G Confirmed to Get 5,500mAh Battery Ahead of India Launch; Price Range Tipped

description: Meta AI is finally rolling out in European countries. The company’s artificial intelligence (AI) chatbot will be available to users in the European Union (EU) nearly 1.5 years after it was first launched. This comes nearly eight months after the Menlo Park-based tech giant stated that the rollout of its AI services in the region will be delayed due to requests from the EU’s Data Protection Authority (DPA).
title: Meta AI Finally Rolling Out in Europe, to Offer Limited Features at First

description: Samsung Galaxy Tab S10 FE series details have surfaced online again. Previous leaks suggested the expected prices of the purported tablets in the US and some of their probable features. A new report has hinted at the likely prices of the Galaxy Tab S10 FE models in Europe and shared leaked design renders of the tablets. Some key specifications of the base Galaxy Tab S10 FE and Galaxy Tab S10 FE+ variant have also been tipped.
title: Samsung Galaxy Tab S10 FE, Tab S10 FE+ Price, Design, Key Features Surface Online Again

description: The European Commission chastised Google for allegedly breaching the bloc’s landmark Digital Markets Act by favoring in-house services across its sprawling search empire and for preventing app developers from steering consumers to offers outside of its Play Store. Meanwhile, Apple was told it must loosen the shackles on its prized iPhone operating system in order to comply with the law
title: Google, Apple Hit by Twin EU Rebuke Amid Big Tech Crackdown

description: Google Pixel 9a was launched on Wednesday as the company’s latest affordable “a” series handset. The phone sits below the flagship models in the Pixel 9 lineup, sacrificing some of the premium features for an affordable price tag. As per a report, Google has confirmed that one of the trade offs is the modem used in the Pixel 9a. The phone features an older Exynos 5300 compared to the Exynos 5400 found in the other Pixel 9 phones.
title: Google Pixel 9a Reportedly Uses Downgraded Modem Compared to Flagship Pixel 9 Models

description: Nvidia and Elon Musk's xAI have joined a consortium backed by Microsoft, investment fund MGX and BlackRock to expand US' AI infrastructure. The consortium renamed itself as AI Infrastructure Partnership on Wednesday.
title: Nvidia, Musk's xAI to Join Microsoft, BlackRock and MGX to Develop AI Infrastructure

description: OpenAI released a new application programming interface (API) for the recently introduced o1-pro artificial intelligence (AI) model on Wednesday. The new API will offer developers better responses than any of the existing models by the AI firm by using more compute. However, the company is passing through the higher computational costs back to the developers by making the API its most expensive offering till date.
title: OpenAI Introduces o1-Pro API for Developers as Its Most Expensive Offering Till Date

description: Ripple CEO Brad Garlinghouse announced that the SEC is dropping its case after four years, crediting the US's new pro-crypto administration for its innovative approach.
title: Ripple CEO Announces End of Four-Year SEC Battle as XRP Surges: Key Details

description: Vivo Y19e was launched in India on Thursday as the latest Y series smartphone from the Chinese brand. The latest model arrives as a budget-friendly offering in two colourways and a single 4GB RAM + 64GB storage option. The Vivo Y19e runs on a Unisoc T7225 processor and boasts a 13-megapixel AI-backed dual rear camera setup.
title: Vivo Y19e With Unisoc T7225 Chipset, 5,500mAh Battery Launched in India: Price, Specifications

description: Apple was ordered by EU antitrust regulators to open up its closed ecosystem to rivals. The move by the European Commission came six months after it opened so-called specification proceedings to ensure that the iPhone maker complies with the Digital Markets Act (DMA) which seeks to rein in the power of Big Tech.
title: Apple Ordered by EU Antitrust Regulators to Open up to Rivals

description: Google Messages is said to be developing a new feature for Android which could potentially make it easier to deal with accidentally sent messages. According to a report, a new remote delete functionality was discovered following an APK teardown of the app’s beta build and it could soon make its way to the Messages app, enabling users to delete messages for everyone in the chat, not just locally on the device.
title: Google Messages Reportedly Developing ‘Delete for Everyone’ Feature for Android

description: iPhone 17 Air is reportedly in the works with a thin build and is speculated to launch in September this year. While there have been several leaks about the design of the iPhone 17 Air, an alleged case render of the upcoming phone has now surfaced online. The render offers hints at the design of Apple's thinnest phone to date. The transparent protective cases indicate a large camera bar cutout at the rear.
title: iPhone 17 Air Leaked Case Render Suggests Pixel-Like Rear Design With Pill-Shaped Camera Module

description: Nvidia released a new family of artificial intelligence (AI) models on Tuesday at its GPU Technology Conference (GTC) 2025. Dubbed Llama Nemotron, these are the company’s latest reasoning-focused large language models (LLMs) that are designed to offer a foundation for agentic AI workflows. The Santa Clara-based tech giant said these models were aimed at developers and enterprises to enable them to make advanced AI agents that can either work independently or as connected teams to perform complex tasks.
title: Nvidia Releases Llama Nemotron AI Reasoning Models for Agentic Workflows

description: Oppo F29 Pro 5G was launched in India on Thursday alongside the Oppo F29 5G. They feature a 360-degree Armour Body and meet military-grade MIL-STD-810H-2022 certification. The base Oppo F29 5G is powered by a Snapdragon 6 Gen 1 chipset, while the F29 Pro version carries a MediaTek Dimensity 7300 Energy SoC.
title: Oppo F29 Pro 5G With MediaTek Dimensity 7300 Energy SoC Launched in India; Oppo F29 5G Tags Along

description: HMD Pulse Pro was launched in April 2024 alongside the Pulse+ and standard Pulse variants. The company could now be working on a successor to the Pulse Pro model. Design renders of an unspecified HMD smartphone have surfaced online, which resembles the HMD Pulse Pro design. Some key features of the purported smartphone have been leaked as well, which suggests it could be the HMD Pulse 2 Pro.
title: New HMD Smartphone Surfaces Online, Possibly the Pulse 2 Pro; Design, Key Specifications Leaked

description: Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 7 and Galaxy Z Flip 7 are said to be in the works and multiple sources have recently hinted at their specifications. As we wait for a possible July launch event, Samsung's 2025 foldables have allegedly been spotted on China's Compulsory Certification (3C) authority, suggesting their charging speeds. The Galaxy Z Fold 7 and Galaxy Z Flip could offer the same charging speed as their predecessors.
title: Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 7, Galaxy Z Flip 7 Listed on China’s 3C; May Offer Same Charging Speed as Predecessors

description: Realme Buds T200 Lite true wireless stereo (TWS) earbuds were launched in India on Wednesday. They debuted alongside the Realme P3 Ultra, Realme P3, and the Realme Buds Air 7. As per the company, the Realme Buds T200 Lite come with a 24 percent larger driver than the previous generation model. The TWS earbuds get IPX4 splash resistance, artificial intelligence (AI)-powered call noise cancellation, and up to 48 hours of battery life on a single charge.
title: Realme Buds T200 Lite With IPX4 Rating, Up to 48-Hour Total Battery Life Launched in India

description: Sony is developing a new, bigger camera sensor that would headline upcoming flagship smartphones, according to claims by a tipster. It is expected to compete against the Samsung ISOCELL HP9 which has been integrated into smartphones such as the Vivo X200 Pro and the Xiaomi 15 Ultra. The purported Sony camera sensor is tipped to function as a main camera sensor and could be used in flagship smartphones which launch later this year.
title: Sony Tipped to be Developing New 200-Megapixel Camera Sensor for Flagship Smartphones

description: South Korea is set to begin testing the Digital Won CBDC for real-world transactions in April, according to local reports citing the Bank of Korea (BoK). The programme will evaluate blockchain technology’s role in finance while allowing the BoK to assess its potential for reshaping the country’s fintech ecosystem.
title: South Korea’s Central Bank to Start CBDC Trials for Real-World Transactions: Reports
